The paper discusses the issue of cyber-attacks and proposes a methodology to evaluate the usability of security APIs. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the sub-category of Computer Security (cs.CR). Additionally, the paper also discusses the mistakes made by programmers while developing software applications, which falls under the sub-category of Software Engineering (cs.SE). The proposed methodology also involves evaluating the usability of security APIs, which is related to the sub-category of Human-Computer Interaction (cs.HC). The paper also discusses the impact of cyber-attacks on day-to-day work, which is related to the sub-category of Social and Information Networks (cs.SI). Finally, the paper discusses the vulnerability of software to cyber-attacks, which is related to the sub-category of Cybersecurity (cs.CY).
